<div class="indented"><a id="comment-10039"></a>
  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/battlestars-daybreak-worst-ending-history-screen-science-fiction#comment-10039" class="active">Sorry</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Tue, 2009-07-14 18:47.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>Firefly, alas, had very poor astrophysics.   Like almost all TV SF, it failed to understand the geometry of space, just how vast and mostly empty it is.  (Douglas Adams said this best.)   You can&#8217;t have hundreds of planets all around a single star which all have human compatible climates, some of them inner and some of them outer.      At best you could have 2-3 gas giants in a habitable zone, each with perhaps a dozen or two habitable moons, but that&#8217;s tough to make work.   </p>

<p>And space is vast.  You would never accidentally run into somebody while moving from planet to planet.  (Each path is different as your target and origin are always moving relative to one another.)   You would not be able to &#8220;hide&#8221; a planet in a nebula.  You could not have phone calls between planets.    There would be some trips that were short (moons of the same planet) and some trips that took hundreds of times longer &#8212; varying with time of year.    The hidden Reaver planet and the big nebula just above another planet that was full of Reaver ships and how you got to the Reaver planet?  That just made no sense at all.  (That&#8217;s Serenity, though, not the TV show, but I consider them the same thing.)</p>

<p>But I do admire Firefly for at least trying to not have FTL.</p>

<p>Sleeping in Light was an OK ending to B5, the 5th season itself (filmed after SIL) was OK but not great.  The original ending, where there never was a Sheridan, and 20 years later B4 reappears and Commander Sinclair (who did all that Sheridan did) goes to it to become Valen, would have been something, I suspect.   They turned that into a regular episode when they had to change out the captains.</p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; </div>
