    <div class="content"><p>I was disapointed by the direction things took and breaking of the producer and audience contract. That's been discussed before so a waste of time going over again. People can mishandle a franchise and lose touch with the audience but beyond that you start getting into naked politics and that can head into self-damage very fast. Under those circumstances it's probably better just to walk away.</p>
<p>You've made some very good points about fanwank and expectations. A revised ending might have standalone merit but it's a lot of work and that effort's probably better off being invested in a new IP. It would have the advantage of not pissing people off and offering something new. I'm no fan of riding someone else's coat tails. It lacks credibility and you could never profit from an IP you don't own in any case.</p>
